In its bid to facilitate interactions with Dubai-based company executives and delegates looking for potential business partners in the Nigerian Market, the Lagos Chamber of Commerce and Industry (LCCI), is set to hold a B2B investment session with exporters and investors from Dubai today. The B2B session which is scheduled to take place today Monday December 17, 2018 by 9am at Eko Hotel and Suites, Victoria Island, Lagos will provide a unique platform for members of the Nigerian Business community to meet and discuss with key decision makers and be on a good pedestal to receive critical advice while asking important questions on doing business in Dubai. Muda Yusuf, Director General of the Lagos Chamber of Commerce and Industry (LCCI) said: “Other important features of this meeting shall include finding Nigerian distributors for Dubai- owned brands, sourcing for Nigerian partners, buyers and importers of goods and services made in Dubai, offering business opportunities to Nigerian entrepreneurs, generating leads for referrals and increasing business opportunities in the United Arab Emirate market.”